entries.title: Brazilian funk is the soundtrack of the World Cup on TikTok, despite the team’s loss
entries.description: Though Brazil lost the quarterfinal to Croatia in the FIFA World Cup, Brazilian Funk carioca music has exploded on TikTok, attracting young and old new fans.

entries.title: How Morocco's surprise World Cup run rallied a legion of Arab fans
entries.description: When Morocco takes the field Saturday for the World Cup’s quarter final, the team will have not just an entire nation behind them, but a legion of fans

entries.title: California woman deported from Russia
entries.description: California woman Sarah Krivanek was deported from Russia. Her departure occurred on the same day as the release of Brittney Griner in a prisoner swap with Russia.

entries.title: Japan, Britain and Italy to build jet fighter together
entries.description: Japan, Britain and Italy are merging their next-generation jet fighter projects in a ground-breaking partnership spanning Europe and Asia that is Japan’s first

entries.title: As 'zero-Covid' nears end, Chinese remember whistleblower doctor Li Wenliang
entries.description: As China moves away from its strict “zero-Covid” controls, there has been a resurgence of online tributes to whistleblower doctor Li Wenliang.

entries.title: Russian opposition politician sentenced to 8.5 years in prison on fake news charges
entries.description: Russian opposition politician Ilya Yashin was sentenced in court to eight-and-a-half years in prison on Friday on charges of spreading “false information”
